<paragraph blockId="13.[143,263,858,882]" box="[143,263,858,882]" pageId="13" pageNumber="908">
<emphasis box="[143,263,858,882]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="908">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[143,1103,897,954]" pageId="13" pageNumber="908">
The specific name of the new species is derived from the Greek 
<emphasis box="[848,894,898,922]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="908">poly</emphasis>
(= many) plus the Latin 
<emphasis box="[211,255,930,953]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="908">spin</emphasis>
(= spine), referring to the female genitalia bearing many spines.
</paragraph>
